Apologies for the error. It seems that the error is occurring because the `HomeComponent` is already declared in the main `AppModule`. To resolve this issue, you need to remove the declaration of `HomeComponent` from the `AppModule` and only include it in the `HomeModule` of the `HomeMicrofrontend`.

Update the `app.module.ts` file in the "MainApp" project to remove the declaration of `HomeComponent`. It should look like this:

```typescript
import { NgModule } from '@angular/core';
import { BrowserModule } from '@angular/platform-browser';
import { AppComponent } from './app.component';

@NgModule({
  declarations: [
    AppComponent
  ],
  imports: [
    BrowserModule
  ],
  providers: [],
  bootstrap: [AppComponent]
})
export class AppModule { }
```

Then, in `HomeMicrofrontend/src/app/home/home.module.ts`, import `HomeComponent` and add the `@Component` decorator to the `HomeComponent` class. Here's the updated code:

```typescript
import { NgModule } from '@angular/core';
import { CommonModule } from '@angular/common';
import { HomeComponent } from './home.component';

@NgModule({
  declarations: [
    HomeComponent
  ],
  imports: [
    CommonModule
  ],
  exports: [
    HomeComponent
  ]
})
export class HomeModule { }
```

Make sure all the required dependencies are imported correctly. After making these changes, rebuild the microfrontend and try again.

If you face any other issues, please let me know.

